Sappi Closes Adamas Paper Mill in South Africa After Reaching Worker Deal

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d
-- 
2011-08-03T10:05:59Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-03/sappi-closes-adamas-paper-mill-in-south-africa-after-reaching-worker-deal.html
Sappi Ltd. (SAP)  said it will shut down its
Adamas paper mill at  Port Elizabeth  in  South Africa  after
reaching an agreement with employee representatives.  The company will take a charge of about $5 million in the
fourth quarter in relation to closure costs, it said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Alastair Reed at 
 areed12@bloomberg.net  